OL,6,FIn her report, she said: "Nationally
OL,7,Fthere is signage once individuals pass
OL,8,Fthrough the gate, but there is limited
OL,9,Fsignage on the gate itself as people
OL,10,Fenter the walkway, only a short
OL,11,Fdistance from the 'decision point'.
OL,13,F"Increasingly, more people wear
OL,14,Fearphones and are therefore less aware
OL,15,Fof their surroundings. Introducing
OL,16,Fclear pictorial signage on the gate,
OL,17,Fbefore individuals enter the 'decision
OL,18,Fpoint' area, such as an image of
OL,19,Fearphones with a line through them,
OL,20,Fmay help alert users at the right
OL,21,Fmoment.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
